<br>
1) Increase the average level of the guild.  Yup...XP and levels.  This is pretty obvious, I think.<br>
2) Better equipment for the guild.<br>
<br>
Number two sounds simple enough and logical enough.  However, to really do it right you need to concentrate on certain targets when raiding.  The MA and SA for the guild should be the two that get the best equipment first!  Look at your MAs equipment list (Chris's magelo, I'm assuming) and see what targets you can raid that will improve the MA's gear.  The MA/SA are very critical and with the best gear will allow the guild to take down bigger Mobs with less wiping.<br>
<br>
A good example would be the Kael arena where we wiped at the end.  Chris went down pretty quickly and after that it was just a domino effect.  If the MA can withstand the BIG BAD GUY for even 30 seconds longer before assist is called, that can change the outcome.  On a really mean critter, that just means that the MA will have an even better chance of surviving a bit longer.<br>
<br>
Thus, guild raids should focus on two things currently.  Targets with good drops for your guild members (not necessarily always for the MA), and if very few members are online...the XP grind.  Some very nice items can be purchased in the bazaar if you want to spend time cash hunting.  Some items can be quested (8th shawl for casters), and still others can be crafted if any in the guild are doing tradeskills.<br>
<br>
So you have a wider range of options than just raiding certain targets for that UBER drop.  I just think the guild may benefit from having a goal that is focused on 1) leveling up and 2) improving equipment.<br>
<br>
This may already be something you are familiar with and is what the guild is focusing on now.  So please don't feel like I'm preaching at you or telling you how to run your guild.  The charter thingy says that you will be a raiding guild though, so I thought I'd waste some of your time by writing this long thing<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Learning to raid as a guild is something to that must be learned also, but from the raids I've attended with you I don't think that's a problem.  Everyone works together as one unit VERY well.  Everyone follows directions and the most important thing of all....you all have a good time doing it.  Sure, you may wipe and have a horrid recovery ahead of you, but I don't see lots of negativity in raid chat or anything.  That is just SO great to see.<br>
<br>
Ok, I think I've rambled on for just about long enough now.  I've got to go see how many more times I can trigger the Death Squad in EW and run for my life<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
